The Role

As a Reporting & Insights Analyst within the Digital Analytics team, your role will be to assist in the transformation of our analytics and reporting capabilities with the Marketing, Media and Acquisition department at Auto & General. You will be tasked with automating existing processes, proactively identifying opportunities for improvement and promoting the democratisation of data and analytics capabilities.

Key Accountabilities

 Transform our analytics and reporting capabilities within the MMA team, moving us from descriptive reporting to interactive analytics and insights;

 Deliver Daily, Weekly, Monthly & Ad-Hoc reports and analysis for the MMA team;

 Automate manual reporting processes using ETL tools and cloud workflows;

 Drive value from enterprise analytics software (Tableau);

 Drive value from integrations between the Enterprise Data Warehouse, data lake, cloud platforms, digital analytics platforms and front-end analysis and reporting solutions;

 Develop robust, reusable and comprehensive datasets for multiple applications;

 Democratise MMA analytics by building beautiful, usable dashboards, visualisations and reports;

 Understand and integrate data from third party marketing applications into custom reports & dashboards & reports; and

 Become the go-to source of knowledge for internal data systems relevant to MMA, policy attribution, and data troubleshooting.

Knowledge And Experience

 2+ years’ experience with enterprise reporting platforms (preferably Tableau);

 Strong familiarity or experience with digital analytics solutions (ie Google Analytics or Adobe Analytics);

 Basic to Intermediate SQL skills; familiarity with SQL and NoSQL databases; 

 Experience with Google BigQuery highly desirable;

 Strong analytical & Microsoft Excel skills;

 Strong communication and business writing skills; ability to translate findings into recommendations;

 Passion for digital marketing & analytics;

 Outstanding ability to think creatively, identify and resolve problems; and

 Excellent analytical, organizational, and time management skills.

Familiarity or experience with (some or all) the below technology will be very highly regarded:

 Google Marketing Platform (Google Analytics / Optimize / Data Studio / SA360 / DV360);

 HTML/CSS/Javascript/Python;

 Google Cloud Platform (e.g. BigQuery / PubSub / DataPrep / DataStore or equivalent);

 Strong fluency or qualifications in data science, maths or statistics;

 Working with a tag management solution (e.g. GTM / DTM / Tealium); and

 Working with optimisation and testing solutions (e.g. Google Optimize / Adobe Target).

Who Are Auto & General

Auto & General is the Australian arm of a private global group with 8,000 employees across 31 offices and over 8.9 million customers worldwide.

In Australia, Auto & General launched in 2000 and has grown to provide industry-leading motor, home and travel insurance products both directly through Budget Direct and via industry leading partnerships. With an Australian team of 1400+ we are now looking for talented individuals who can help drive our ambitious growth plans.

Our Benefits

 Toowong - City fringe location

 Enjoy additional leave days - ‘ME’ leave and ‘Volunteer Day’ leave;

 Join our vibrant social and community activities including annual celebration, family fun days and regular events across each of our sites;

 Study support (up to 50% of tuition fees for relevant courses) and professional membership reimbursement;

 Employee discounts on Car, Home, Travel insurance, Roadside Assistance;

 Income protection insurance provided to support you in the event of non-work related illness or injury;

 Discounts with a broad range of providers, including gym memberships, accommodation, dental care and more.

